  "text": "Exponential backoff retry patterns are implemented across three major Go repositories:\n\n**Kubernetes/Kubernetes** implements exponential backoff in two primary locations:\n1. The goroutinemap package (pkg/util/goroutinemap/exponentialbackoff/exponential_backoff.go) provides the ExponentialBackoff type that manages retry timing with an initial duration of 500ms and a maximum cap of 2 minutes 2 seconds, doubling on each error.\n2. The wait package (staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/) provides the high-level ExponentialBackoff() function that wraps exponential backoff logic around condition checking. The Backoff struct in backoff.go defines configurable fields: Duration (initial wait), Factor (exponential multiplier), Jitter (random variance), Steps (max iterations), and Cap (maximum duration).\n\n**Grafana/Grafana** implements exponential backoff for alert rule evaluation (pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/schedule.go) through the RetryConfig struct embedded in SchedulerCfg. Configuration is managed via pkg/setting/setting_unified_alerting.go with parameters: initial_retry_delay (default 1s), max_retry_delay (default 20s), and randomization_factor (default 0.1). This was introduced in PR #99710 to support retry with backoff in alert rule evaluation.\n\n**Prometheus/Prometheus** implements exponential backoff for remote write operations in two key files:\n1. queue_manager.go contains sendWriteRequestWithBackoff() which manages retries for write requests to remote endpoints, doubling the backoff duration on each retry from min_backoff (default 30ms) up to max_backoff (default 100ms). It respects HTTP Retry-After headers and disables resharding during backoff periods.\n2. client.go defines the RecoverableError type that wraps errors with optional Retry-After durations, and classifies HTTP status codes to determine which errors are eligible for retry (5xx, 429 Too Many Requests) versus which should fail immediately (4xx except 429, 2xx)."
}

